Subject: Re: [T2] smoke

On Tue, 6 Aug 2002, Daniel Peysner wrote:

> when first starting the engine,  in the morning say. there appears to
> be some smoke that comes out of the exhaust, but it only does
> it once when starting up . does anyone have any ideas as to what this
> could be ?


Blue smoke?  Probably worn valve guides.  The oil in the rocker box will
seep down the valve stems into the intake and exhaust ports when sitting.
When you start it up, that oil burns off.

Not (nessicarily) a major concern.

....david

